    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"long_descriptions_container\"></div></div><div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <div class=\"standalone_image qti-align-center\"><img alt=\"Graph of the function T on in the x y plane. Refer to long description.\" aria-describedby=\"LDC-UII000000_01\" src=\"/images/6f2df122a841b4f248fd298b7233c028.svg\"><div aria-label=\"Long description for graph of T\" class=\"sr-only qti-visually-hidden\" id=\"LDC-UII000000_01\" role=\"region\">\n<p class=\"dap_body\">The horizontal axis represents the variable h and has the label Hours. It ranges from 0 to 24 in increments of 6. The vertical axis is labeled Temperature with values in degrees Fahrenheit. It ranges from 0 to 70 in increments of 5. All coordinates are approximate. Moving from left to right:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The curve begins at (0 comma 35).</li>\n<li>The curve increases to reach a high point at (12 comma 65) before decreasing back to (24 comma 35).</li>\n<li>The curve appears to be symmetric about the vertical line h = 12.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><p class=\"dap_body\">​During a month in a certain town, the temperature increases and decreases over the course of a day. A graph of the average temperatures during that month for any given day is shown. The data in the graph can be modeled by the function&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"T\"><math alttext=\"T\"><mi>T</mi></math></span>, where&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"T open parentheses h close parentheses\"><math alttext=\"T open parentheses h close parentheses\"><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mi>h</mi></mfenced></math></span>&nbsp;gives the temperature, in degrees Fahrenheit (<span aria-label=\"degrees F\"><math alttext=\"degrees F\"><semantics><mrow><mo>°</mo><mtext>F</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>), at time&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"h\"><math alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math></span>&nbsp;hours after midnight. At a certain point in that month, there is an adjustment to clocks for daylight saving time, at which point clocks are adjusted&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>&nbsp;hour forward. For example,&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"6\"><math alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn></math></span>&nbsp;a.m. instantly becomes&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"7\"><math alttext=\"7\"><mn>7</mn></math></span>&nbsp;a.m. The function&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\"><mi>D</mi></math></span>&nbsp;models the same data as function&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"T\"><math alttext=\"T\"><mi>T</mi></math></span>, after the shift to daylight saving time. If&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"h\"><math alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math></span>&nbsp;still represents the number of hours after midnight, which of the following defines&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"D open parentheses h close parentheses\"><math alttext=\"D open parentheses h close parentheses\"><mi>D</mi><mfenced><mi>h</mi></mfenced></math></span>&nbsp;in terms of&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"T\"><math alttext=\"T\"><mi>T</mi></math></span>&nbsp;?</p> </div> </div> </div>\n",
